WEBVTT


00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:03.160
We are just a few days out for the 2024 parliamentary election

00:00:03.161 --> 00:00:03.961
here in Korea.

00:00:03.962 --> 00:00:07.741
There are 40 registered parties participating in the election.

00:00:07.800 --> 00:00:09.320
I have compiled a series of videos

00:00:09.321 --> 00:00:10.961
to let you know where the parties stand

00:00:10.962 --> 00:00:14.041
on the issues. Over the next few days will be taking a deep dive.

00:00:14.042 --> 00:00:17.361
I have compiled a series of videos for the 14 parties

00:00:17.362 --> 00:00:19.161
that returned their election manifestos

00:00:19.162 --> 00:00:20.701
to the National Elections Commission.

00:00:20.760 --> 00:00:23.360
And I have translated their top 10 election pledges into English

00:00:23.361 --> 00:00:24.401
for everybody today.

00:00:24.402 --> 00:00:26.281
Let's take a look at the progressive camp.

00:00:26.282 --> 00:00:28.801
The largest progressive party participating in this election

00:00:28.802 --> 00:00:30.441
with six seats in Parliament

00:00:30.442 --> 00:00:32.201
is the Green Justice Party.

00:00:32.202 --> 00:00:34.281
They are an electoral alliance of the Green Party

00:00:34.282 --> 00:00:37.121
and the Justice Party. Their election pledges include

00:00:37.122 --> 00:00:39.521
applying the Labour Standard Act to workplaces

00:00:39.522 --> 00:00:42.881
with under five workers, expanding the Ministry of women and family

00:00:42.882 --> 00:00:44.861
to the Ministry of Gender Equality,

00:00:44.960 --> 00:00:47.080
installing public care centers in all communities,

00:00:47.081 --> 00:00:48.181
towns and villages,

00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:51.200
eliminating tuition fees for students in national universities,

00:00:51.201 --> 00:00:53.941
creating public medical universities and public hospitals,

00:00:54.080 --> 00:00:56.600
enacting a comprehensive anti discrimination law,

00:00:56.601 --> 00:00:59.681
enacting a Green New Deal in going carbon neutral by 2050,

00:00:59.682 --> 00:01:01.161
guaranteeing the rights of the disabled

00:01:01.162 --> 00:01:02.901
through the institutionalization,

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.000
the right of movement and other rights

00:01:05.001 --> 00:01:07.861
and guaranteeing 1 million Green New homes.

00:01:07.960 --> 00:01:10.920
The next party participating in the election is the Progressive Party.

00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:14.680
they are in an electoral alliance with the centrist Democratic Party,

00:01:14.681 --> 00:01:17.601
but they are competing in some district elections.

00:01:17.602 --> 00:01:20.121
But Their candidates are tied to the Democratic Party

00:01:20.122 --> 00:01:22.521
on national proportional representation lists.

00:01:22.522 --> 00:01:24.001
Their election manifesto includes

00:01:24.002 --> 00:01:26.121
a disillusion of the prosecutor's office,

00:01:26.122 --> 00:01:28.561
introduction of a presidential runoff voting system,

00:01:28.562 --> 00:01:30.461
believing debt of the common people,

00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:33.920
increasing taxes on the ultra wealthy for wealth redistribution,

00:01:33.921 --> 00:01:36.481
nationalizing essential energies, water,

00:01:36.482 --> 00:01:40.241
electricity and gas. The opposition of the construction of new airports

00:01:40.242 --> 00:01:42.541
and instead working on public railways,

00:01:42.680 --> 00:01:45.440
guaranteeing housing by strengthening public rentals,

00:01:45.441 --> 00:01:49.681
a four day 32 hour work week and enacting a anti discrimination law,

00:01:49.682 --> 00:01:51.841
Equality Act in the Lifetime Partnership Law.

00:01:51.842 --> 00:01:52.921
The third progressive party

00:01:52.922 --> 00:01:55.801
participating in this national election is the Labour Party.

00:01:55.802 --> 00:01:58.161
They have one district candidate in Ursan

00:01:58.162 --> 00:02:01.401
and two candidates for proportional representation nationally.

00:02:01.402 --> 00:02:04.801
They believe in things such as creating a citizens right to recall

00:02:04.802 --> 00:02:07.081
lawmakers, getting rid of district elections

00:02:07.082 --> 00:02:08.241
in favour of full

00:02:08.242 --> 00:02:10.581
proportional representation for the National Assembly,

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:13.580
abolishing the requirements to establish political parties,

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:16.080
including the allowing of coalition parties

00:02:16.081 --> 00:02:17.761
and regional political parties

00:02:17.762 --> 00:02:19.981
and abolition of the National Security Act,

00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:22.760
allowing teachers and public officials to join political parties

00:02:22.761 --> 00:02:24.301
and engage in political activities.

00:02:24.440 --> 00:02:26.360
Creating an economy centered around democracy,

00:02:26.361 --> 00:02:29.241
ecology and care, combating the climate crisis,

00:02:29.242 --> 00:02:31.141
unemployment crisis and care crisis,

00:02:31.320 --> 00:02:34.240
increasing the corporate tax by at least 40%,

00:02:34.241 --> 00:02:37.081
stopping the privatization of electricity and gas

00:02:37.082 --> 00:02:38.321
and making sure labor rights,

00:02:38.322 --> 00:02:39.921
jobs and living wages are guaranteed

00:02:39.922 --> 00:02:42.841
through a major shift in the labor and employment policies.

00:02:42.842 --> 00:02:45.281
The last progressive party participating is the farmer

00:02:45.282 --> 00:02:46.481
and Fisherman's Party.

00:02:46.482 --> 00:02:49.521
They support Universal basic income for farmers and fisherman.

00:02:49.522 --> 00:02:51.961
They support establishing a National Food Sovereignty Committee.

00:02:51.962 --> 00:02:54.641
They want 30% eco friendly agriculture.

00:02:54.642 --> 00:02:56.721
They want to include farmers and fisheries

00:02:56.722 --> 00:02:59.321
in the Disaster Compensation Act.

00:02:59.322 --> 00:03:01.801
They want to increase housing for farmers and fishermen.

00:03:01.802 --> 00:03:05.921
And they want a massive increase in care and government policies

00:03:05.922 --> 00:03:07.941
dedicated to creating female farmers.

00:03:08.120 --> 00:03:11.160
They also want to expand basic rights for easing of employment

00:03:11.161 --> 00:03:12.981
permit system for migrant workers.

00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:15.559
Join us next time when we discuss the Liberal camp.
